{{Infobox artwork | image_file = KMM Maillol.JPG | painting_alignment = Front | image_size = 300px | title = Air | alt = | other_language_1 = | other_title_1 = | other_language_2 = | other_title_2 = | artist = [[Aristide Maillol]] | year = 1938 | type = lead | height_metric = | width_metric = | length_metric = 93.3 | height_imperial = 50 | width_imperial = 94 | length_imperial = {{frac|36|3|4}} | diameter_metric = | diameter_imperial = | city = various | museum = | coordinates = | owner = }} '''''Air''''' is a lead or bronze sculpture, by [[Aristide Maillol]].
He modeled [[Dina Vierny]] in plaster in 1938, and casts were made after his death. It is an edition of six.<ref>{{cite book |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=JPdxHlnx-z4C&pg=PA108&lpg=PA108&dq=air+maillol&ct=result&resnum=7 |title=The Fran and Ray Stark collection of 20th-century sculpture at the J. Paul Getty Museum |author=Antonia Boström |author2=Christopher Bedford |author3=Penelope Curtis |author3-link=Penelope Curtis |author4=John Dixon Hunt |publisher=Getty Publications |year=2008 |isbn=978-0-89236-904-1}}</ref> Examples are located at the [[Kröller-Müller Museum]], [[Yale University Art Gallery]], [[Jardin des Tuileries]], [[J. Paul Getty Museum]],<ref>[http://siris-artinventories.si.edu/ipac20/ipac.jsp?session=1O21373608JY4.13676&limitbox_1=LO01+%3D+ias&menu=search&aspect=Keyword&npp=50&ipp=20&spp=20&profile=ariall&ri=50&source=~%21siartinventories&index=.NW&term=+68360015+&aspect=Keyword&x=11&y=13#focus Air, (sculpture)]. ''SIRIS''</ref> [[Norton Simon Museum]],<ref>http://www.nortonsimon.org/collections/browse_artist.php?name=Maillol%2C+Aristide&resultnum=1</ref> and [[Kimbell Art Museum]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.kimbellart.org/Collections/Collections-Detail.aspx?prov=false&cons=false&cid=8658 |title=Archived copy |access-date=2011-11-23 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120423215203/https://www.kimbellart.org/Collections/Collections-Detail.aspx?prov=false&cons=false&cid=8658 |archive-date=2012-04-23 |dead-url=yes |df= }}</ref>
