{{Infobox museum | name = Kidzu Children's Museum | native_name = | native_name_lang = | image = Inside Kidzu Children's Museum.jpg | caption = | alt = | map_type = | map_caption = | map_alt = | established = March 2006 | dissolved = | location = [[Chapel Hill, NC]] | type = Children's museum | collection = | visitors = | director = Lisa Van Deman | president = | curator = | publictransit = | car_park = | network = | website = http://www.kidzuchildrensmuseum.org/ }}
'''Kidzu Children's Museum''' is a private, 501(c)(3) non-profit children's museum serving ages infant through tween. The museum was established in 2006 in a store front on [[Franklin Street (Chapel Hill)|Franklin Street]] in [[Chapel Hill, North Carolina]]. The museum soon outgrew the location and began looking for a larger space. In November 2011, after construction delays pushed back the move to a larger space, the museum temporarily moved to University Square. Then in February 2014, Kidzu reopened in [[University Place (Chapel Hill, North Carolina)|University Place]] in Chapel Hill. They are contracted to stay in the mall through 2017.<ref>[http://www.kidzuchildrensmuseum.org/aboutus/ourstory Our Story]</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=White|first=Corinne|title=Kidzu Children's Museum rises above construction delay|url=http://www.dailytarheel.com/index.php/article/2011/09/kidzu_rises_above_construction_delay|accessdate=3 January 2012|newspaper=Daily Tar Heel|date=2011-09-13}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Lindenfeld Hall|first=Sarah|title=Kidzu Children's Museum's opening delayed|url=http://www.wral.com/lifestyles/goaskmom/blogpost/9704001/|newspaper=WRAL}}</ref>
